The '''Pan-American Students Conference''' was a student conference held in [[Bogotá]], [[Colombia]], in April 1948. The conference was organized in opposition to the [[Pan-American Conference]] also held in Bogotá.<ref>pp. 105 Martin</ref> The conference was attended by a young [[Fidel Castro]].

On April 8 an organizational meeting in office of the [[Confederation of Workers of Colombia]]. A second meeting is claimed to have happened on April 9.<ref>pp. 22 Cova</ref> Not long after that Gaitán was shot,<ref>pp.23 Cova</ref> leading to the [[Bogotazo]].

