{{Infobox Journal | title = Journal of Palestine Studies | cover = | editor = [[Rashid Khalidi]] | discipline = [[Middle Eastern studies]]; [[Israeli–Palestinian conflict]] | language = English | abbreviation = J. Palest. Stud. | publisher = [[University of California Press]] | country = USA | frequency = Quarterly | history = Founded 1971 | openaccess = No | license = | impact = | impact-year = | website = http://www.palestine-studies.org/jps | link1 = http://www.palestine-studies.org/ | link1-name = Institute for Palestine Studies Homepage | link2 = http://ucpressjournals.com/journal.php?j=jps | link2-name = Homepage at University of California Press | RSS = | atom = | JSTOR = | OCLC = 757505811 | LCCN = | CODEN = | ISSN = 0377-919X | eISSN = 1533-8614 | boxwidth = }} The '''''Journal of Palestine Studies''''' is an [[academic journal]] established in 1971. It is published and distributed by [[University of California Press]] on behalf of the [[Institute for Palestine Studies]] (IPS). The current editor is [[Rashid Khalidi]] of [[Columbia University]].<ref>[http://ucpressjournals.com/journal.asp?j=jps&jDetail=editorial University of California] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20071011182701/http://ucpressjournals.com/journal.asp?j=jps&jDetail=editorial |date=2007-10-11 }} Journal of Palestine Studies current editorial staff.</ref>
The journal is the oldest English language journal devoted exclusively to Palestinian affairs and the [[Arab–Israeli conflict]]. It includes information on the region's political, religious, and cultural concerns. The IPS has been described as "independent and internationally renowned" and the journal is refereed.<ref>[https://books.google.com/books?id=gl2SAgAAQBAJ&pg=PA185&lpg=PA185 Global Scholarship in International Relations, edited by Arlene B. Tickner, Ole Wæver], page 185</ref>
==Content== The journal contains: * Feature articles * Interviews * Book reviews * Quarterly updates on conflict and diplomacy * A settlement monitor * Detailed chronologies * Documents and source material * Bibliography of periodical literature.<ref>[https://www.jstor.org/journal/jpalestud ''Journal of Palestine Studies'' – About Journal]; [[JSTOR]]</ref>
==Commentary== {{quote|There is of course, a great mass of custom-tailored information in books, newspapers and magazine articles. Unfortunately, most of these fall into the categories of pro-Israeli or pro-Palestinian propaganda or disinformation ... The exceptions, however deserve the highest praise; whatever their stance or political orientation, their concern was primarily with information and understanding ... The other exception is the ''Journal of Palestine Studies'', published and edited by Hisham Sharabi since 1971, a quarterly magazine that is critically pro-PLO, but invaluable in its documentation of the PLO position. Unfortunately, no comparable journal exists yet in Israel.|[[David Kimche]], former Director-General of the Israeli Foreign Ministry, writing of sources "on our relations with the Palestinians"<ref>{{cite book |author=[[David Kimche|Kimche, David]] |title=The Last Option: After Nasser, Arafat & Saddam Hussein: The Quest for Peace in the Middle East |publisher=[[Charles Scribner's Sons]]; Maxwell Macmillan International |location=New York City |year=1991 |pages=322–323 |isbn= 978-0-684-19422-6}}</ref>}}
